Мне не хватило! 😭 верните меня обратно и оставьте там подольше 😭 Но ведь и вправду говорят, что лучше недо-, чем пересыщение 😌 В таком случае в 98% случаев вы останетесь с положительными эмоциями 😍🙌 Время быстротечно и нужно уметь радоваться обстоятельствам, обстановке и событиям сейчас, в эту самую минуту ⏰

A week ago i set out on a journey to atone and redeem myself,with no intention or hope of coming back.i was ready for my sentence; it was going to be the end ...the punishment would not have been decided by me but would have been brought about my own doing.

No one forced me to seek that sentence--in fact the ones i thought would do so wanted me to lie or to bargain--but i felt it was my obligation and my choice.Religious beliefs aside, it was about taking responsibility for my mistakes despite their consequences.

Apparently that was enough.
True regret is the way to redemption.Truly wanting to accept the punishment for those mistakes(basically being ready die for my sins)..owning up and not running from the sentence is apparently enough to release me.And what i want to do from here is apparently enough to redeem me.

The beauty of #hudud,a law system that is often misconstrued as convoluted or barbaric.This way you ensure i regret what i do, am motivated to never repeat it and still be of future use to society.

After all, the best punishment for a sinner willing to die is to keep on living and spend the rest of their life atoning by doing good.
Ps Assumption is the seed of mistakes and misunderstanding, so dont assume.
1.There is #wisdom behind hudud and im seeing it..it's not what it seems.its harshness is to deter you from doing it in the first place.
When the mistake is done, it's meant for your repentance..if you truly regret your mistake and want to never repeat it..regret it so much that you want to be punished for it..that's your redemption.

2.you will make mistakes.and these mistakes will likely hurt others.their mistakes will
hurt you.best you can do is makeup for it(if you can),
apologise(regardless of whether they need to as well), forgive(whether or not they did), do good and not repeat the same mistakes.or try not to.
And try to help others so they dont do the same.

A week ago i chose the end, didn't want this chance.
I was given it anyway--because I didn't want it,delicious irony--and in that time I've figured out how i want to spend my lifehelping people.
Didnt want this chance im given but won't waste it.
I know where to go from here.

"Grasping at Straws"
I cleaned my room yesterday and found an old stack of papers with poems I never posted on here. They're all in scribbles, you can tell the words were coming to my mind too fast to write them down because my handwriting is so sloppy 😜
I think I remember writing this one during a time when either myself or someone close to me needed to find the strength to go on.

Throwback to a day of creation. In meditation I am a creature of light and you four are little balls of sunshine bouncing around me. In case of emergency I will pick you up, tuck you in between my ribs, curl up around you and make you invisible to any eyes of evil. To see you fly freely is my highest wish but know this, for as long as the echo of my voice can be heard you will never fly alone.

When you respect yourself others will follow, without cherishing dignity we're empty vessels. Without a soul to achieve the crown. Anyway like, share, tag... Even follow my friend's travel page @mikey_yeahh_buddy if need be. Enjoy 👌🏼👌🏼
